# SentinelOne LinuxOS Agent Uninstallation Guide
><br />Only users with Management Console uninstall permissions can remove the Agent. It is important to thoroughly understand a userâ€™s reason before you respond to a request.<br /><br />

## 1. Uninstalling Agent from the Management Console 
-  Select one or more endpoints.<br />
   -  &nbsp; **1) Sentinels** > **2) ENDPOINTS** > **3) Select endpoint** ![Agent Selcet](./img/linux/uninstall1.png)<br /><br />
- Uninstall the agent from the selected endpoint:
   -  &nbsp; **1) Actions** > **2) Actions Endpoint** > **3) Uninstall.**<br />![Actions Agent](./img/linux/uninstall2.png)<br /><br />
   - Complete the 2-factor authentication(2FA) to uninstall it from the console. Authentication is valid for 30 minutes, and re-authentication is required to perform actions again.<br />![Complete 2FA](./img/linux/uninstall3.png)
<br /><br /><br />

## 2. Uninstalling Agent From the CLI

<!-- ### Follow these steps to uninstall the Linux Agent with CLI
1. Save or copy the passphrase.
   - Some Agent features, such as CLI uninstall, require a passphrase.
   - If Anti-Tampering is enabled, you must have the Agent passphrase to uninstall the Agent with the CLI.
2. Log in to the endpoint permissions: sudo for macOS, root or sudo for Linux, Administrator for Windows.
