### To uninstall the Linux Agent with sentinelctl CLI
***Note:*** *A reboot is not required. You can install the Agent again immediately after the uninstall.*
- **To get the passphrase for an endpoint from the Management Console:** <br />
  - Supported from Agent version: Windows 4.2 | Legacy Windows 2.0 | macOS 4.2 | Linux 4.2 | K8s 4.2 
  - &nbsp; **1) Actions** > **2) Agent Actions** > **3) Show Passphrase.**<br />![Show Passphrase](./img/linux/uninstall4.png)<br /><br />
  - The Passphrase opens in a new window. ![Show Passphrase](./img/linux/uninstall5.png)<br /><br />

- **Run the command to uninstall the agent and enter the password.**
  - Log in as root (sudo is not enough).
  - Run the sentinelctl command : `/opt/sentinelone/bin/sentinelctl control uninstall` > *input_your_`<passphrase>`*
      ```bash
      [root@localhost SentinelOne]$ sudo /opt/sentinelone/bin/sentinelctl control uninstall 
      Enter passphrase : <input_your_passphrase>
      Uninstalling agent...
      Stopping agent...
      Agent stopped
      Successfully uninstalled agent.
      ```